bio.info: Permic is a dragon that was previously a lizard because of an experiment. He's mostly rude and stubborn, but can be nice at times. He has dark red scales, grey fingerless gloves, and pink shoes.
bio.backstory: Permic used to be a lizard, rather than a dragon, for 13 years. Then, just after his 14th birthday, he wandered off to a lab that turns regular creatures into mythical ones. He was dosed with some suspicious medicine, but didn't feel anything, so he went to bed. The next morning, however, he felt different. He had horns on his head and he had gained the ability to breathe fire (He always had the pyrokinesis abilities since he was a lizard dw about that). He had been turned into a dragon. His first reaction was to find a way to get back into his older form, but he hasn't been able to do so. He has gotten used to this new form, however he does still look for ways to get back to his older form.

bio.info: A tamoan chihuahua who is usually very nice and active, but can be overconfident and cocky at times. He has yellow-orange fur, green shoes, and a blue collar. He is mostly clueless about the world around him, but he would really like to explore it more and make friends along the way.
bio.backstory: Sparky's from Planet Tamoa. He has been living in his hometown for 11 years. It has been very peaceful and happy in that hometown, until it was attacked and war broke out. The president of the town instructed the youth to evacuate the planet to a partner planet via an emergency space ship. Sparky's trip was going fine, until the space ship started going out of his control and went crazy, and ended up crashing on the planet called Yaretza. He was seriously injured from the crash but thanks to somebody healing him, he was able to recover. The events still come in his mind at times, but he stays calm and acts like it never happened most of the time.

bio.info: A man with three spirits of separate identity, mind, and control. 3'9 in height. likes to explore on his own. Prefers to be alone, he feels his identities can hurt. Guilty for things out of control, but with great cover up, as a __trick__, hence 'Sutela'. Likely to hide emotions, yet ends up being like a magnet for people (relevant in the future).
bio.backstory:
He was born with multi-spirituality, from weakness. __The Ascended__, finally born. It was a secret kept to his parents. He was forced to not reveal the secret. Yet he gathered friends with it. But at 16, it was revealed, ~~from rumors~~.

```The Ascended, from Mythology of Ventrah: someone on an illegal state of ascension, growing in spiritual force. Never meant to exist, met with hatred.
Maturity, harmony, and confidence, grants them infinitude.``` 

Ventrah locals were ready for a hunt, by greed, and is still active. He had to run away. (Yaretza - dimensional travel).
bio.voice:
__Neutral (Sunburn)__: Pheonix Wright (Ace Attorney)
__Laut__: Commander Shepard (Mass Effect)
__Tempus__: Aang (Avatar TLA)
bio.likes: Peace and quiet (unless used to chaos), tea, solitude (sometimes), friends (when solitude inapplicable)
bio.dislikes: The feeling of weakness, disruptions of his normal lives, overly bad jokes, seeing people being in pain
bio.fears: To be found __again__ by ones with a specific intent, horror-like situations
bio.\"a:
A man of three identities, with the ability of changing between them, on accident. Tho they're pretty subtle right now, they can strengthen in a way or another. 3'9 in height, a guy that likes to explore on his own, or not try and spend time with the group. He prefers to be alone because of identity issues and how he believes it can hurt other people. A man of regrets, feeling guilty for a lot of things, but with great ways to cover that up, as a trick, hence 'Sutela'. A stoic, distant person with trust issues, hence why he likes to leave groups whenever he feels like it.

EDIT: As of now he is getting a lot better with himself. He still hides stuff but he is going to be a lot more open about it.

bio.info: A cheerful Tanuki and somewhat egotistical, and has perfectionist tendencies. He wears a slightly loose, blue short-sleeved turtleneck to match his Brown fur with dark tan cargo shorts. And a utility belt where he keeps his shortsword around his waist. He may resemble Spectra in many ways, both being Tanukis, but Sky's tail is slightly larger, as well as being a bit fluffier. He seems to have an empty look in his eyes, though it's hard to discern.
bio.backstory: As a traveling warrior, he's seen many places and people. Through these travels, he has gained battle experience by simply mimicking what others do. Sometimes you can spot him with a leaf on his head. Being a Tanuki, he gets rather lonely, as there is almost no fellow Tanuki in the world. Spectra is the only exception to this, but as she came from a different planet, it's a bit awkward for him to approach her.

healquote: Do you know what you do in this predicament, when life hui-tcha's you? You go AGAIN!
killquote: Now that's what I'm talkin' about.
deathquote: Sometimes in life, you try to hit life with a 'hui-tcha', but then life decides to hit you with a 'hui-tcha.

bio.info: A friendly and mischievous shark, Gawr Gura often plays around with her chumbuds and fellow team members. Best compared to a friend that exchanges back and forth teasing and encouragement. Despite being an over 9000 year old shark, she cleverly uses jokes and simple humor as she hangs out with friends.
bio.backstory:
A descendant of the Lost City of Atlantis, who swam to Earth while saying, ''It's so boring down there LOLOLOL!''
She bought her clothes (and her shark hat) in the human world and she really loves them. In her spare time, she enjoys talking to marine life.

bio.info: Sakuya has dark blue eyes, silver hair, a long braid on each side of her face with green bows at the ends, and she carries many knives. She wears a pink and dark blue French maid's outfit with long sleeves, and a white maid headband on her head. The Roman numerals for 1 through 12 line the bottom of her apron.

bio.info: A Blue Shoutmon who dawns a Purple (and long) Scarf and a familiar Blue/Cyan vest.  Unlike your average Shoutmon however, he wields a sort of Keyblade modeled after the Star Sword instead of the usual Mic. You shouldn't underestimate him however, he packs quite a punch in battle.

A T-Rex with cyan scales that is much smaller than the average size of his species. He has a rather serious but kind mood most of the time, but due to not being told much by the scientists who revived him from his fossil, he doesn't know much about the current technology.
bio.likes: Kind creatures, friends
bio.dislikes: Creatures that are hostile for no reason
